Dialogue: 10,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.75,Caption,,0,0,0,,Here's the decision that matters. When\Nthe engineers wrote
Dialogue: 10,0:00:03.75,0:00:07.50,Caption,,0,0,0,,the software for that system, they\Ndidn't start from
Dialogue: 10,0:00:07.50,0:00:11.66,Caption,,0,0,0,,scratch. Why would they? Ariane 4's\Nversion had flown for
Dialogue: 10,0:00:11.66,0:00:15.83,Caption,,0,0,0,,years without a single fault. It was\Ntrusted. It was
Dialogue: 10,0:00:15.83,0:00:16.25,Caption,,0,0,0,,proven.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:16.59,0:00:18.13,Caption,,0,0,0,,So they reused it.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:18.47,0:00:22.04,Caption,,0,0,0,,And that decision — the safe one, the\Nsensible one
Dialogue: 10,0:00:22.04,0:00:24.18,Caption,,0,0,0,,— is what killed the rocket.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:24.52,0:00:28.73,Caption,,0,0,0,,To understand why, you need one small\Npiece of how
Dialogue: 10,0:00:28.73,0:00:31.68,Caption,,0,0,0,,computers hold numbers. I'll keep it\Npainless.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:32.02,0:00:35.90,Caption,,0,0,0,,Inside that navigation software was a\Nvalue tracking the
Dialogue: 10,0:00:35.90,0:00:39.36,Caption,,0,0,0,,rocket's sideways speed — its horizontal\Nvelocity. The
Dialogue: 10,0:00:39.36,0:00:43.24,Caption,,0,0,0,,program stored it in a large, roomy\Nformat: a
Dialogue: 10,0:00:43.24,0:00:47.13,Caption,,0,0,0,,sixty-four-bit number, able to hold a\Nhuge range of
Dialogue: 10,0:00:47.13,0:00:47.56,Caption,,0,0,0,,values.
